<subSubSection id="C370656FFF90FFA5FF5B4A1E55F2FA4F" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD536E4FF90FFA5FF5B4A1E55F2FA4F" blockId="28.[151,1436,1303,1509]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
This genus consists of only two species— 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D67FF90FFA5FDA74A1E5561FAF9" box="[619,793,1340,1365]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Apathya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cappadocica">
<emphasis id="B91EEAF6FF90FFA5FDA74A1E5561FAF9" box="[619,793,1340,1365]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">A. cappadocica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D67FF90FFA5FC834A1E55AEFAF8" baseAuthorityName="Nilson, Rastegar-Pouyani, Rastegar-Pouyani &amp; Andren" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[847,982,1340,1364]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Apathya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="yassujica">
<emphasis id="B91EEAF6FF90FFA5FC834A1E55AEFAF8" box="[847,982,1340,1364]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">A. yassujica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Recent phylogenetic study of the genus brought an evidence of exceptionally high level of intraspecific variation among populations (recognized as distinct subspecies) of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D67FF90FFA5FE544AA6555AFA31" authority="(Kapli et al. 2013)" baseAuthorityName="Kapli" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[408,802,1412,1437]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Apathya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cappadocica">
<emphasis id="B91EEAF6FF90FFA5FE544AA6543FFA31" box="[408,583,1412,1437]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">A. cappadocica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B15FF90FFA5FD9A4AA65562FA31" author="Kapli, P. &amp; Botoni, D. &amp; Ilgaz, C. &amp; Kumlutas, Y. &amp; Avci, A. &amp; Rastegar-Pouyani, N. &amp; Fathinia, B. &amp; Lymberakis, P. &amp; Ahmadzadeh, F. &amp; Poulakakis, N." box="[598,794,1412,1437]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="992 - 1001" refId="ref55674" refString="Kapli, P., Botoni, D., Ilgaz, C., Kumlutas, Y., Avci, A., Rastegar-Pouyani, N., Fathinia, B., Lymberakis, P., Ahmadzadeh, F. &amp; Poulakakis, N. (2013) Molecular phylogeny and historical biogeography of the Anatolian lizard Apathya (Squamata, Lacertidae). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 66, 992 - 1001. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2013.05.009" type="journal article" year="2013">
Kapli 
<emphasis id="B91EEAF6FF90FFA5FD524AA754AFFA31" box="[670,727,1412,1437]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Even more interesting was the phylogenetic position of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D67FF90FFA5FF5B4A8A575AFA13" baseAuthorityName="Nilson, Rastegar-Pouyani, Rastegar-Pouyani &amp; Andren" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[151,290,1448,1471]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Apathya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="yassujica">
<emphasis id="B91EEAF6FF90FFA5FF5B4A8A575AFA13" box="[151,290,1448,1471]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">A. yassujica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which was nested within 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D67FF90FFA5FD9A4A8A550AFA13" baseAuthorityName="Lantz &amp; Suchow" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[598,882,1447,1472]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Apathya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="cappadocica" subSpecies="urmiana">
<emphasis id="B91EEAF6FF90FFA5FD9A4A8A550AFA13" box="[598,882,1447,1472]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">A. cappadocica urmiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a sister group to its Iranian populations and rendering 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D67FF90FFA5FEC54AEE57CFFA49" box="[265,439,1484,1509]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Apathya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cappadocica">
<emphasis id="B91EEAF6FF90FFA5FEC54AEE57CFFA49" box="[265,439,1484,1509]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">A. cappadocica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
paraphyletic with respect to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D67FF90FFA5FD304AEE55FBFA48" baseAuthorityName="Nilson, Rastegar-Pouyani, Rastegar-Pouyani &amp; Andren" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[764,899,1484,1508]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Apathya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="yassujica">
<emphasis id="B91EEAF6FF90FFA5FD304AEE55FBFA48" box="[764,899,1484,1508]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">A. yassujica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
